  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Life Saving Food Assistance to Extremely Vulnerable Nigerian IDPs in Borno and Yobe States, including Blanket Supplementary Feeding for Children at Risk aged 6-23 months</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main aim of this project is to provide life saving food assitance to newly identified food insecure people in the newly accessible aeras.  This will be done through cash based transfers for 63,000 food insecure people for three months, through in kind food distribution for 150,000 people in IDP camps where markets are not functioning and through supplementary feeding for 64,000 children between 6 and 23 months old.</narrative>
  </description>
